Coca-Cola Femsa to Build $160 Million Plant in Colombia

-- B y   T h o m a s   B l a c k
-- 
2011-05-06T21:06:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/coca-cola-femsa-plans-160-million-bottling-plant-in-colombia.html
Coca-Cola Femsa SAB (KOFL) , Latin America’s
largest soft-drink company, plans to build a $160 million
bottling plant in Colombia, said Jose Castro, director of
 investor relations .  The plant will be located in the northern area of Bogota
and will begin operations in three to five years, he said in a
telephone interview today. The company yesterday announced it
will build a $146 million bottling plant in Brazil.  In Colombia, shipments of carbonated drinks, flavored water
and water rose 5.2 percent in 2010 to 244.3 million unit cases
from 232.2 million in 2009, according to company’s financial
reports.  The plant in Brazil will be located in the state of  Minas
Gerais  and have annual production capacity of 2.1 billion liters
by 2015, the company said yesterday in a statement. Castro
declined to provide the production capacity of the Colombian
plant.  With the investment in the two plants, Chief Financial
Officer Hector Trevino said that the company will boost its
original capital expenditure plan by $60 million to $620 million
this year. He spoke during a conference call April 27.  Coca-Cola Femsa rose 44 centavos to 92.7 pesos in Mexico
City trading today. The shares have declined 9.3 percent this
year.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Thomas Black  in Monterrey
at   tblack@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Jonathan
Roeder at   jroeder@bloomberg.net  